Instruction: With battery inserted and all switches ON, open control module 3 and use a voltmeter referenced to the PSU negative. (1) Measure continuity from module 2 local 0V to module 3 local 0V, and from module 3 local 0V to module 4 local 0V, to see if the return path is broken inside or around module 3. (2) With power on, measure voltage from the PSU negative to the two output cables of module 3 to verify whether either is actually connected to the global 0V or floating. This will determine if a break or misconnection exists in the 0V line through module 3.
